tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Finished T51 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Played in four Web.com Tour events...In his first start, at the Nova Scotia Open, recorded the first top-10 of his career...Low round of the week came in the second round with a 66...Closed with weekend rounds of 69-69 for a T10...Qualified for the U.S. Open at Chambers Bay and finished T27 after an opening-round 67 left him in a T4.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Finished his career at the University of Illinois with four individual titles...Was named Ping second-team All-American and All-Midwest Region in 2014...Also named Big Ten Player of the Year in 2014 as well as earning All-Big Ten first-team honors...Helped lead the Illini to back-to-back NCAA regional titles in 2014-15.
tourBios.personal: Attended Mater Dei High School in Santa Ana, Calif...His brother, Derek, played for the University of California baseball team and was drafted by the Philadelphia Phillies...Earliest and favorite golf memory was winning his first event for a $100 gift card.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2016 is T8th at the El Bosque Mexico Championship presented by INNOVA.
